            <title type="html">Compile flags for gfortran</title>
            <author><name>Thomas Spura</name></author>
            <link href="/blog/2012/gfortran-flags.html"/>
            <updated>2012-04-29T17:45:00Z</updated>
            <published>2012-04-29T17:45:00Z</published>
            <id>/blog/2012/gfortran-flags.html</id>
                        <category   scheme="/blog/tags"
                        term="fortran"
                        label="Fortran" />
            
            <content type="html">
                
                &lt;p&gt;When compiling Fortran, you cannot be sure, that gfortran sees the code the
same way like you. For instance, when you assign &lt;code&gt;1.&lt;/code&gt; to a &lt;code&gt;real(8)&lt;/code&gt; variable
and don&amp;#8216;t notice, that &lt;code&gt;1.&lt;/code&gt; is only &lt;code&gt;real(4)&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But when compiling with some flags from this blog, gfortran will warn you about
such&amp;nbsp;issues.&lt;/p&gt;            </content>
